caption: Awesome boned tail. Squid, beans, all delicious. Good atmosphere. Attentive staff. We will repeat for sure.

A different option in Vitoria. Everything we ordered was good and the service was impeccable. The furniture is a little dull and the upholstery of the chairs needs to be changed, which makes you not completely comfortable.

Very good experience overall. We had not reserved and they gave us a table without problems. Excellent attention from everyone and very friendly. They recommended us to try the typical dessert, Goxua, what a delight! Highly recommended

The treatment received from the waiter was horrible. We were 8 people but in the end one got sick and didn't come, because he reproached us for that, we arrived 15 minutes later than the time and he reproached us for it, we ordered a part of 7 menus and more things off the menu and he also thought it was bad...

I was having some beers with my wife and some friends and I thought it was great. It's deceiving at first but then it's very good. The waiter who served us was friendly and very attentive. Keep it up guys
A must visit to this Fortress, which gives us spectacular views of the city and the Guadiana!!! Space where events and concerts are held.

A must-see, despite some drawbacks The Pantheon is a must-see monument in Rome, impressive for its architecture and history. It's definitely worth the visit, but skip-the-line tickets are essential to avoid interminable waits. The price is high for a relatively quick visit (about 15 minutes on site), and it gets very crowded inside, which somewhat spoils the atmosphere. It's worth it, but be prepared.
Watch out! There is a hole in the roof!
It's impressive to see it in person, we just had the opportunity to see it on a rainy day when the rain was coming inside.
Very nice place. I only visited it from the outside. You have to pay to get in, and on a weekday there weren't many lines.
I visited recently and absolutely loved it! It is marvelous and so architecturally advanced for when it was made. It is the oldest fully intact building in Rome! It is a must visit and so amazing!
